            <h2>ðŸš€ Autonomous Systems Hit the Road</h2>
            <p class="cluster-intro">From highways to human brains, autonomous systems are achieving milestones that signal production readiness</p>
            
            <div class="article-card">
                <h3><a href="https://www.teslarati.com/tesla-fsd-successfully-completes-full-coast-to-coast-drive-with-zero-interventions/?utm_source=tldrnewsletter" target="_blank">Tesla FSD Successfully Completes Full Coast-to-Coast Drive with Zero Interventions</a></h3>
                <div class="article-meta">
                    TLDR: Science & Futuristic Technology
                    <span class="read-time">2 min read</span>
                </div>
                <div class="article-summary">A Tesla owner successfully drove coast-to-coast across the US on Full Self-Driving (FSD) Supervised with zero interventions during the trip. Their Model 3 completed the drive in 2 days and 20 hours, starting at the Tesla Diner in Los Angeles, CA, and ending in Myrtle Beach, SC. It was accomplished with Tesla FSD V14.2 on AI4 hardware. The milestone trip was widely lauded by members of the Tesla community.</div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="article-card">
                <h3><a href="https://links.tldrnewsletter.com/YZ7kYF" target="_blank">Neuralink Will Start High-Volume Production of Brain-Computer Interface Devices in 2026</a></h3>
                <div class="article-meta">
                    TLDR: Science & Futuristic Technology
                    <span class="read-time">1 min read</span>
                </div>
                <div class="article-summary">Neuralink received FDA breakthrough device designation for its speech restoration in 2025. The company also launched clinical trials in the Middle East and the UK, and completed two surgeries in Canada. It upgraded its surgical robot to be able to insert an electrode thread every 1.5 seconds at insertion depths of over 50mm. Neuralink plans to move to an almost completely automated surgical procedure this year.</div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="cluster">
            <h2>ðŸ¤– The Agent-Powered Builder Revolution</h2>
            <p class="cluster-intro">AI agents are rewriting the rules of who can build software and how security professionals protect it</p>
            
            <div class="article-card">
                <h3><a href="https://links.tldrnewsletter.com/pzNUXP" target="_blank">How I Code with Agents, Without Being 'Technical'</a></h3>
                <div class="article-meta">
                    TLDR: Programming, Design & Data Science
                    <span class="read-time">18 min read</span>
                </div>
                <div class="article-summary">Ben Tossell, who works at Factory, a company developing a frontier software development agent, has spent 3 billion tokens in four months through an agent without writing any code. None of the code was read, but Tossell read the agent output religiously, which led to him picking up a ton of knowledge around how code works, how projects work, where things fail, and where they succeed. Tossell has shipped several projects using his method over the past few months, including a personal site, a 'wrapped' product for Factory, several custom CLIs, and an AI-directed video demo system.</div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="article-card">
                <h3><a href="https://danielmiessler.com/blog/cybersecurity-ai-changes-2026?utm_source=tldrnewsletter" target="_blank">Here Are the Major Changes I See Coming for Cybersecurity in 2026</a></h3>
                <div class="article-meta">
                    TLDR: Programming, Design & Data Science
                    <span class="read-time">10 min read</span>
                </div>
                <div class="article-summary">The primary security question for companies will be how good their attackers' AI is versus their own AI. There will be increased spending on agentic security platforms and significantly more in-house building of security tools. Asset management will become possible for the first time because of agents. Most security platforms will eventually be replaceable with AI prompts.</div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="article-card">
                <h3><a href="https://github.com/max-sixty/worktrunk?utm_source=tldrnewsletter" target="_blank">Worktrunk</a></h3>
                <div class="article-meta">
                    TLDR: Quick Links
                </div>
                <div class="article-summary">Worktrunk is a CLI for git worktree management designed to run AI agents in parallel.</div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="article-card">
                <h3><a href="https://www.nerd-lang.org/about?utm_source=tldrnewsletter" target="_blank">NERD</a></h3>
                <div class="article-meta">
                    TLDR: Quick Links
                    <span class="read-time">3 min read</span>
                </div>
